{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "A look at the engines behind modern technology, how they transform data into decisions, and the creative possibilities they unlock for everyone.",
    "title": "Artificial Intelligence: Machines That Reason"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "At its heart, this field focuses on building systems that mimic human problem-solving. Instead of following rigid, pre-written instructions, these models find patterns in vast amounts of data to make predictions, generate content, or categorize information on their own.",
      "title": "What intelligent systems actually do"
    },
    {
      "description": "Algorithms do not just crunch numbers; they learn by example. By showing a system millions of labeled images, it identifies the features of a cat without being told what ears or whiskers look like, proving that complex concepts can emerge purely from statistical relationships.",
      "title": "The power of learning from examples"
    },
    {
      "description": "These tools are woven into your day, from how your email filters spam to how medical scanners spot diseases earlier than human eyes. This course builds the technical literacy required to distinguish between hype and the genuine mechanisms that power these breakthroughs.",
      "title": "How intelligence is embedded in your world"
    },
    {
      "description": "Beyond programming, this space invites designers, ethicists, researchers, and engineers to shape how we interact with technology. Whether you want to build creative tools, audit fairness in systems, or automate complex workflows, the practical skills covered here provide the foundation for your own projects.",
      "title": "Your role in building the future"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Uma visão sobre a lógica por trás da vida, desde o funcionamento das células até a complexidade dos ecossistemas globais.",
    "title": "A ciência da vida"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "A biologia observa o que diferencia um organismo vivo de um objeto inanimado. Ela investiga como os seres buscam energia, crescem, se reproduzem e respondem ao ambiente ao seu redor.",
      "title": "O que define a vida"
    },
    {
      "description": "O DNA funciona como um manual de instruções biológico universal. Essa molécula armazena as informações que constroem cada detalhe de um organismo, permitindo que a vida passe suas características através de gerações.",
      "title": "Como o código da vida funciona"
    },
    {
      "description": "Nenhum ser vivo existe de forma isolada. A sobrevivência depende de redes intrincadas, onde pequenos microrganismos, plantas e animais interagem em equilíbrios frágeis que sustentam todo o planeta.",
      "title": "A conexão entre todos os seres"
    },
    {
      "description": "Quem se dedica a essa área atua em diversas frentes, como a preservação ambiental, o desenvolvimento de novas tecnologias de saúde, a segurança alimentar e a descoberta de tratamentos para doenças complexas.",
      "title": "Onde a biologia atua na prática"
    },
    {
      "description": "Ao longo deste curso, você conectará esses princípios fundamentais para interpretar fenômenos biológicos, desenvolvendo um olhar analítico sobre os mecanismos que mantêm o mundo natural funcionando.",
      "title": "O caminho que percorreremos"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "A look at the rules governing the smallest parts of our universe, where intuition meets the bizarre reality of subatomic physics.",
    "title": "The strange world of the subatomic"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Quantum mechanics describes how particles like electrons and photons behave. Unlike the predictable world of billiard balls, the tiny world relies on probabilities, meaning objects exist in multiple states at once until they are observed.",
      "title": "The shift from certainty to probability"
    },
    {
      "description": "One of the most striking phenomena is entanglement, where particles become linked regardless of distance. Changing the state of one instantly affects the other, a concept that once baffled Einstein and remains a cornerstone of modern experiments.",
      "title": "Particles connected across distances"
    },
    {
      "description": "This field drives today's high-tech landscape. From the transistors inside your smartphone and the lasers in medical equipment to the promise of unhackable communication networks, quantum principles make modern digital life functional.",
      "title": "How quantum physics powers your daily life"
    },
    {
      "description": "Physicists and engineers apply these principles to solve complex problems in materials science, cryptography, and computing. This course provides the mathematical and conceptual toolkit to navigate these advanced scientific frontiers.",
      "title": "Navigating the quantum frontier"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "The rules that turn abstract laws into real-world results. Discover how courts navigate conflicts and why the process of litigating a case is often as decisive as the law itself.",
    "title": "The Rules of the Legal Game"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Law is not just about what is right or wrong, but about how a dispute moves from a complaint to a resolution. Civil procedure provides the roadmap for courts to hear evidence, summon witnesses, and enforce decisions fairly.",
      "title": "Why procedure defines justice"
    },
    {
      "description": "A court cannot hear just any case. A judge must have both the authority over the people involved and the power to rule on the specific type of conflict. Without this jurisdiction, a court is just a room, not a tribunal.",
      "title": "How courts get the power to decide"
    },
    {
      "description": "Before a trial begins, both sides trade information through discovery. This phase prevents 'trial by ambush' by forcing parties to reveal their evidence early, which frequently encourages settlements long before a jury is ever empaneled.",
      "title": "The power of discovery"
    },
    {
      "description": "Lawyers, judges, and clerks use these rules to manage everything from corporate class actions to neighbor disputes. This course will demystify the mechanics behind the courtroom, giving you a clear view of how legal arguments translate into binding authority.",
      "title": "Connecting the rules to real cases"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Una mirada a cómo diseñamos los lugares donde transcurre nuestra vida y los hilos invisibles que conectan calles, edificios y personas.",
    "title": "La ciudad como organismo vivo"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "El urbanismo no trata solo de edificios, sino de las reglas del juego que dictan cómo nos movemos, convivimos y habitamos el espacio público día tras día.",
      "title": "Mucho más que arquitectura"
    },
    {
      "description": "Las ciudades con mejor diseño funcionan como sistemas naturales: fomentan la caminabilidad, la cercanía a servicios básicos y la interacción social espontánea.",
      "title": "Por qué algunas calles se sienten mejor que otras"
    },
    {
      "description": "Desde la planificación del transporte hasta la gestión de áreas verdes, los urbanistas resuelven el rompecabezas de cómo hacer que millones de personas coexistan con eficiencia y bienestar.",
      "title": "El trabajo de transformar entornos urbanos"
    },
    {
      "description": "Al dominar los principios de la escala humana y la resiliencia urbana, este curso te dará las herramientas para analizar, proponer y mejorar la habitabilidad de tu entorno cotidiano.",
      "title": "Tu papel en el futuro de la ciudad"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Un regard neuf sur les objets, les images et les monuments qui structurent notre vision du monde, pour découvrir comment le passé façonne notre présent visuel.",
    "title": "Au-delà de la surface des images"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "L'histoire de l'art ne consiste pas à mémoriser des dates ou des noms de peintres. C'est une enquête sur les intentions humaines, les enjeux politiques et les émotions qui poussent une civilisation à transformer la matière en message durable.",
      "title": "Ce que cache une œuvre d'art"
    },
    {
      "description": "Chaque époque impose ses contraintes, qu'il s'agisse de la rareté des pigments, des règles religieuses ou des révolutions industrielles. L'art est souvent la réponse ingénieuse aux limites techniques et sociales de son temps.",
      "title": "L'art comme solution technique"
    },
    {
      "description": "De la conception d'interfaces numériques à la muséographie ou la conservation, les méthodes d'analyse visuelle permettent de décoder les influences qui dictent le design, la publicité et l'architecture de nos villes modernes.",
      "title": "Décoder le design de notre quotidien"
    },
    {
      "description": "Ce parcours vous donnera les outils pour lire le langage des formes, des couleurs et des compositions, transformant votre regard sur n'importe quel objet, du musée à la rue.",
      "title": "Développer un regard critique et curieux"
    }
  ]
}
